cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper discusses the evaluation of data visualization techniques, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The methodology proposed in the paper involves the use of machine learning models, specifically deep convolutional neural networks, to compare the efficiency of different visualization techniques. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning models for evaluation also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper focuses on graph visualization techniques, which could be classified under graphics (cs.GR).
